generated_description:  Frankenthaler's "Santa Fe II" (1986) exemplifies Color Field painting, emphasizing color and form over narrative. Created during the post-war era, it reflects a shift towards abstraction and emotional expression. The expansive pink and blue hues evoke a vast sky, capturing the essence of the American Southwest. This work highlights Frankenthaler's contribution to abstract art, bridging Abstract Expressionism and Color Field painting through innovative techniques and vibrant palettes.
