generated_description:  Mary Fedden's "Zebra" (2007) blends Fauvist bold colors with still-life and animal imagery. The vibrant red backdrop contrasts starkly with the zebra, symbolizing nature's wildness amidst domesticity. The fruit and bottle foreground evoke traditional still-life themes, yet the zebra introduces an unexpected, surreal element. This juxtaposition reflects contemporary art's exploration of nature and human environments, challenging conventional boundaries. Fedden's work captures a modern sensibility, merging tradition with innovative vision.
