generated_description:  Jacopo Bellini's "Virgin with Child" (c. 1450-1500) exemplifies Early Renaissance devotion, blending Gothic spirituality with emerging humanism. The Madonna's serene expression and the Christ Child's playful gesture reflect a tender maternal bond. The book symbolizes divine wisdom, while the ornate frame and angelic backdrop emphasize sacredness. This work bridges medieval traditions with the Renaissance focus on naturalism and emotional depth, showcasing Bellini's role in transitioning Venetian art towards greater realism and color richness.
