generated_description:  Max Weber's "Russian Ballet," a Cubist piece from 1915, captures the dynamism of modern dance. Reflecting early 20th-century fascination with non-Western cultures, it uses fragmented forms and vibrant colors to evoke the energy of ballet. The overlapping planes and geometric abstraction challenge traditional perspective, mirroring the era's rapid social and technological changes. This work symbolizes the avant-garde spirit of the time, blending cultural influences with innovative artistic techniques. Context insufficient for deeper symbolic analysis.
