generated_description:  Martiros Saryan's "Mules Laden with Hay" (1910) embodies Fauvism's bold use of color and simplified forms. Set against a vibrant yellow backdrop, the green hay and blue-clad figures evoke the sun-drenched landscapes of the Caucasus. This scene reflects early 20th-century rural life, emphasizing labor and tradition. Saryan's expressive palette and dynamic composition celebrate the region's cultural identity and natural beauty, aligning with Fauvism's focus on emotional intensity over realistic representation.
