generated_description:  Martin Schongauer's "Madonna on the Turf Bench" (c. 1450-1500) exemplifies Northern Renaissance piety. The intimate portrayal of Mary and Christ, set against a serene landscape, reflects the era's focus on personal devotion. Schongauer's detailed engraving technique captures the tender bond between mother and child, emphasizing Christian themes of maternal care and salvation. The signature "M†S" confirms his authorship, showcasing his mastery in religious iconography and influencing later artists.
