generated_description:  This Chagall work, reflecting his engagement with biblical narratives, depicts Joshua before the angel of the Lord, a scene from the Hebrew Bible. Created in the mid-20th century, it embodies Chagall's unique blend of naive art and primitivism. The angel, wielding a sword, symbolizes divine authority and protection. Chagall's Jewish heritage informs the piece, merging personal spirituality with universal themes of faith and leadership. The stark, monochromatic palette enhances the dramatic tension and spiritual gravity of the encounter.
