generated_description:  Olivier Debré's "Touraine Automne Jaune Rose" (1950-2000) exemplifies Color Field painting, emphasizing color and form over narrative. Debré's abstracted landscapes reflect post-war existentialism, capturing nature's essence through vibrant hues. The yellow and rose tones evoke autumn warmth, while vertical forms suggest trees, blending human perception with natural rhythms. This work challenges traditional representation, aligning with mid-20th-century artistic shifts towards abstraction and emotional expression. Contextual details are limited.
