generated_description:  This 1934 Cubist work by Albert Gleizes, "Matière et Lumière ou le Christ au tétramorphe," blends Christian iconography with abstract forms. The central figure, likely Christ, is surrounded by symbols of the four Evangelists, reflecting theological themes. Gleizes' use of overlapping planes and vibrant colors exemplifies Cubism's exploration of space and light, merging spiritual and modernist aesthetics during a period of artistic experimentation post-WWI. The piece underscores the era's search for new ways to express traditional subjects.
